	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, after a simple search . . i found this:<br><br>==================================================<br>Remains of Master Tynn<br>Trakrons Teeth: Your Location is -2800.04, 2785.07, -337.77<br>Crusader Vragor regards you indifferently -- what would you like your tombstone to say?<br>You say, 'Hail, Crusader Vragor'<br><br>Crusader Vragor says 'Perhaps you would care to hear a tale, and perhaps you could help me with the ending. It is the tale of the end of Grandmaster Tynn. We all know that Tynn came into Sebilis with no rebirth. I suppose you know he created the caste of Iksar monks, but I doubt you know where he now rests do you? '<br><br>You say, 'no'<br><br>Crusader Vragor says 'Then I shall tell you. Master Tynn chose a place of rest in his old age. While deep in meditation he slipped away and breathed no more. His corpse remained in the stance of meditation for many years unyielding to the elements. This brings us to recent times. A Trakanasaur that has been named Zhaoku came along the remains and devoured them. The bones too hard to be chewed, he swallowed them whole. To this day he wanders with them lodged in his stomach. Are you interested in knowing where Zhaoku is? '<br><br>You say, 'yes'<br><br>Crusader Vragor says 'I will tell you but you must help me first. I have been tied to this plane because of deeds unfinished. I was questing for the stupendous tome for ages to no avail. Without this tome I can not pass on in peace. Finish my quest, bring me the stupendous tome and a crusader coffin (purchased in Cabilis). I will tell you where the beast rests before I pass on. I doubt you can finish this, but I can always hope. '<br>You hand Crusader Vragor a Stupendous Tome and a coffin<br><br>Crusader Vragor says 'The tome! I can finally pass on in peace. Before I go I will tell you that Zhaoku rests to the east of here near Old Sebilis. He is gigantic and not easily missed.' Crusader Vragor vanishes into a mist, his sigh of relief the only thing left behind. respawn time is approx. 25-30min <br><br>Zhaoku spawns<br><br>Info about Zhaoku:<br><br>cons:yellow to 57, cons red to 56, so he was level 59. <br>Location: if you follow the wall like your on the way to OS, once you get to the wall leading to OS arches follow that in toward the arch....but Dont go through the arch to the ruins, keep following the wall past arch but go slower, he spawns right there in the corner just past arch. Didnt get a loc because druid insta aggroed him....grrr....hi hi no prep spells. <br>Hits really fast without slow in. Slow landed right off the bat with no debuffs in by a 56 shaman. I didnt have log on but I think he was hitting for a high of about 200'ish but usually 70-140 range. Slow wore off when he was at about 30 percent hitpoints ( and monk died ~ ). So if you have small group ( we had 3 people ) you might need to reslow. <br>Snare and Root would not land even with druid and shaman debuffs in, there was no invulnerable message, but slow landed twice no resists, jbb landed for most part with some partial resists, and not one root or snare. <br>..You have looted a Thule Touched Bones... <br><br>Which ID as the remains of Tynn. <br>==================================================<br><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Kurrleeeci/Tynn.html" target=_new>http://www.geocities.com/Kurrleeeci/Tynn.html</a><br><br><br><br><br>and also...<br>==================================================<br>Stupendous Tome Quest<br>PART I<br>First you must collect 6 scrolls from the following places:<br>I: Kaesora Temple in the field of bone - the &quot;failed crypt raider&quot; drops scroll number I<br>II: This scroll can be found in the City of Mist on a spectral courier<br>III: same as II<br>IV: same as II<br>V: This scroll can be found in Castle Mistmore located in faydark. It drops off the dark librarian, who is located to the right when you go through the double doors near the entrance to the castle. Head up the stairs there, and into the library <br><br>VI: This scroll can also be found in Mistmoore. Rather than going right after you enter the double doors, head left, up some stairs. The hallway turns right. Take the 1st left to face a small hallway with a gargoyle on the end. Enter the room on the left and pass through that room and continue to the small bedroom which has a bed with red drapery on it. The ASSISTANT dark librarian drops the 6th scroll. <br><br>PART II <br>After collecting the scrolls, you must see and free the imprisoned Argest.<br><br>Sugggestion - a shrink potion, and some invis potions will help greatly in Droga, since with shrink, you can walk right through the gates/grates. <br><br>Argest, the lost and imprisoned crusader is located in Droga's Temple, located at pos 3400, pos 2900 of the Frontier Mountains. Fall into the pit near the entrance. follow the long cave staying along the RIGHT wall until you come to a small overpassing bridge. Go under this bridge, turn left at end and stay LEFT after that until you get to the JAIL. Then kill many, many penskeepers and penmasters (and their place holders) until you obtain all the keys listed below: <br><br><br>bone key <br>bone necklace key <br>stone key <br>bronze key - note, you don't need to turn this in, it only helps getting to him. <br>Next use the keys to get to the inner jail area. Now wait until an iksar prisoner wearing gold chain type armor spawns in the iksar jail cell (during daytime). This is Argest. <br><br>Give him the 4 keys and recieve the dagger looking object which will operate the stupendous machine he mentions (directly across in the main jail area, looks like a pottery wheel) <br><br>Take the 6 scrolls and the dagger object from Argest, combine all 7 in the machine and recieve a &quot;stupendous tome&quot; lore, no drop. <br>==================================================<br><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Kurrleeeci/StupendousTome.html" target=_new>http://www.geocities.com/Kurrleeeci/StupendousTome.html</a><br><br><br>That should help some, it also gives everything that the quest giver sais.&nbsp;&nbsp;Im still looking for more info, as in.. what to the Thule Bones do?  what are they used for.. etc.. etc..<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jun 27 05:48:31 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>0_o</td></tr>
